    <stitle>HYDRO-MAX&#8482; BRAKE BOOSTER AND MASTER CYLINDER - INSTALL - PRESSURE DIFFERENTIAL SWITCH</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>PRESSURE DIFFERENTIAL SWITCH</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s04017y_14.xml" xrefid="f0401707">Figure 7</hotlnk>
            for all items in parentheses.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Thread pressure differential switch (Item 8) into the master cylinder (Item 6). Tighten to
                10 to 15 lbf-in (1.1 to 1.7 N&#8226;m).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect wiring harness pressure differential switch connector (Item 7) to the pressure
                differential switch (Item 8).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect battery ground cable and unblock the vehicle wheels.</para>
        </step1>
        <para>Check to make sure the warning light on the vehicle instrument panel is off when the engine is running.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
